15/12/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Transport Minister Miron Mitrea marked the end of the first phase of a project to upgrade the air traffic control centre Friday (12 December).
"The country now has the most modern air control facility in Southeast Europe," Mitrea said during the ceremony.
The cost of the whole project is estimated at 150m euros.
The control system covers 17 airports in Romania and a regional direction centre in Bucharest.
(Rompres - 15/12/03)
